oai_dc:dc.dc:title: EFFECT OF CHANNEL DEEPENING ON SALINITY IN THE JAMES ESTUARY
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Nichols, Maynard M.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: channel deepening
salinity
James Estuary
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The effect of a 10-foot channel deepening on the salinity distribution and net flow were studied m the James Estuary to predict estuarine-wide changes that might disturb the natural conditions favorable to oyster production. A hydraulic model was employed to determine the physical changes; then the potential biological consequences were evaluated by integrating the model data with corollary field and laboratory observations.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 11 (1968): Proceedings of 11th Conference on Coastal Engineering, London, United Kingdom, 1968.; 92
